'''Suijin-sai''' (水神祭) refers to: * A {{ill|festival|ja|祭|12=draft|12=draft}} dedicated to the {{ill|water deity|ja|水神|1=Suijin|lt=water god|12=draft|12=draft}}. * A ceremonial event in {{ill|boat racing|ja|競艇|12=draft|12=draft}}, which is detailed in this article.
== Overview ==
In the context of {{ill|boat racing|ja|競艇|12=draft|12=draft}}, '''Suijin-sai''' is a celebratory event where a {{ill|boat racer|ja|競艇選手|12=draft|12=draft}} who achieves a milestone victory, such as their first win, is thrown into the water by fellow racers.
The basic criteria for holding a Suijin-sai are as follows:<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oj6KQKk522g What is Suijin-sai? │ BOATSCOOP] - Official {{ill|BOAT RACE|ja|ボートレース|12=draft|12=draft}} YouTube Channel</ref>: * First victory after debut<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mAKGx7ZxPMQ BOAT RACE Heiwajima - First Victory Suijin-sai & Award Ceremony for Racer 5019 Momoe Shibata] - YouTube, Official Channel of {{ill|Heiwajima Boat Racecourse|ja|平和島競艇場|12=draft|12=draft}}, May 9, 2018</ref>, first championship, or first entry into a final race (初優出). * First win or first championship in major events like {{ill|SG (boat racing)|ja|SG|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|GI (boat racing)|ja|GI|12=draft|12=draft}} tournaments<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sRpCXcxe4FQ SG 29th Grand Champion – Suijin-sai for Kazuki Yanagisawa] - YouTube, Official Channel of {{ill|Tamagawa Boat Racecourse|ja|多摩川競艇場|12=draft|12=draft}}, June 25, 2019</ref>. * Milestone victories such as 1,000th or 2,000th win. * Retirement ceremonies.
The earliest recorded Suijin-sai was for {{ill|Yutaka Imamura|ja|今村豊|12=draft|12=draft}}, inducted into the BOATRACE Hall of Fame, held after his debut race on May 7, 1981.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://yutakaimamura2992.com/|title=Yutaka Imamura Retirement Special Site|work=BOAT RACE Tokuyama|accessdate=2022-05-31}}</ref>
A video from the 1982 {{ill|MB Memorial|ja|MB記念|12=draft|12=draft}} shows {{ill|Ikuo Hikosaka|ja|彦坂郁雄|12=draft|12=draft}}, who had already won six SG titles, participating in a Suijin-sai, indicating that the event was not limited to milestone races but also celebrated major title victories.
Similar ceremonies are held at the {{ill|Boat Racer Training School|ja|ボートレーサー養成所|12=draft|12=draft}} for students who win league competitions or graduation commemorative races, known as the {{ill|Training School Champ|ja|養成所チャンプ|12=draft|12=draft}}.
The event typically takes place at the edge of the pit area facing the water, or from rescue boats where racers are thrown into the water. Sometimes, for fan service, it is performed in front of the audience.
The most common style of Suijin-sai is the "Ultraman Style," where the celebrated racer is lifted in a face-down position and thrown into the water. Other variations exist, and it's common for not only the honoree but also some of the throwers to end up in the water.
== Related Articles == * {{ill|Boat racing|ja|競艇|12=draft|12=draft}}
== External Links == * [http://www.kyotei.or.jp/ BOAT RACE Official Website]
